OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F379A1778324573
OL,3,CNew mum cuddles hours-old baby monkey
OL,4,Cstill with umbilical cord attached
OL,6,FA baby Barbary macaque monkey has been
OL,7,Fphotographed just hours after it was
OL,8,Fborn, still with the umbilical cord
OL,9,Fattached.
OL,11,FIts mum holds her precious new arrival
OL,12,Fclose to her chest at Trentham monkey
OL,13,Fforest in Stoke-on-Trent, where it is
OL,14,Fthe first arrival of the 2026 breeding
OL,15,Fseason.
OL,17,FThe monkey was born high up in the
OL,18,Ftrees in the early hours of Wednesday
OL,19,F29 April, and since then, three more
OL,20,Fof the endangered species have been
OL,21,Fborn.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G1/5
